'''''Story of a Discharged Prisoner''''' (<U+82F1><U+96C4><U+672C><U+8272>; lit. "True Colors of a Hero") is a 1967 [[Cinema of Hong Kong|Hong Kong film]] directed by [[Patrick Lung Kong]].

The film partially inspired the 1986 [[John Woo]] film ''[[A Better Tomorrow]]'', which has the same Chinese name.

